com.intel.fightclub.dialog.state

Interface CUIListener

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    CUIListenerWrapper

    public interface CUIListener
    An interface for receiving callbacks for when the DialogManager instance has finished initialization, changed state, or when an ASR or TTS output is available to be processed.

    • Method Detail

      • onRegistered

        void onRegistered(@NonNull
                  CUIState state)

        This is called when a CUIListener instance is registered with the DialogManager. This provides a CUIState object which contains information about the current state of the CUI.

        This is guaranteed to be called before any other callback.

        Parameters:
        state - The current state of the CUI.

      • onPlatformStateChanged

        void onPlatformStateChanged(@NonNull
                            CUIPlatformState state)
        Notifies when the CUI state has changed.
        Parameters:
        state - The current state of the CUI.

      • onUserStartSpeaking

        void onUserStartSpeaking()
        Notifies when the user has started speaking.

      • onUserStopSpeaking

        void onUserStopSpeaking()
        Notifies when the user has stopped speaking. This does not necessarily imply that the speech recognition engine detected speech.

      • onUserSpeechRecognized

        void onUserSpeechRecognized(@NonNull
                            java.lang.String utterance,
                            double confidence,
                            boolean isLowConfidence)
        Notifies when the speech recognition engine has detected speech from the user.
        Parameters:
        utterance - The utterance that was spoken by the user.
        confidence - The confidence value for that utterance.
        isLowConfidence - Whether or not the utterance is considered to be low confidence.

      • onCoachStartSpeaking

        void onCoachStartSpeaking(@NonNull

        Parameters:
        utterance - The utterance that is being spoken by the coach.

      • onCoachStopSpeaking

      • onLpalToggled
